00:43:54,131 --> 00:43:55,424
Her instinct is to start

822
00:43:55,507 --> 00:43:57,176
with this, "Blame America.

823
00:43:57,259 --> 00:43:58,260
I'm the victim."

824
00:43:58,594 --> 00:44:00,846
Speaking her mind can get her in trouble.

825
00:44:00,929 --> 00:44:02,139
An angry woman.

826
00:44:02,222 --> 00:44:03,849
She's not warm and fuzzy.

827
00:44:03,932 --> 00:44:05,684
She's adding fuel to the fire.

828
00:44:05,768 --> 00:44:08,646
Michelle must think
about what she's become in her life.

829
00:44:10,939 --> 00:44:13,400
I stopped talking off-the-cuff.

830
00:44:13,484 --> 00:44:15,569
I stopped talking freely.

831
00:44:15,653 --> 00:44:17,655
I used teleprompters.

832
00:44:17,946 --> 00:44:19,907
I had to be much more scripted

833
00:44:19,990 --> 00:44:22,159
than I had ever been before.

834
00:44:23,619 --> 00:44:27,039
I was just, sort of, waking up to...

835
00:44:28,540 --> 00:44:31,960
the truth of who we can be:

836
00:44:32,878 --> 00:44:36,048
so ready to assume the worst in people.

837
00:44:37,966 --> 00:44:41,261
The only thing I can do
is share that that does hurt.

838
00:44:42,096 --> 00:44:44,431
Because if we walk around
pretending like it doesn't hurt,

839
00:44:44,723 --> 00:44:47,101
the perpetrators just say,
"Oh, I was just joking.

840
00:44:47,393 --> 00:44:48,936
It's just politics."

841
00:44:49,061 --> 00:44:50,646
It's, like, "No, no. No, no.

842
00:44:50,729 --> 00:44:54,650
That changes the shape
of a person's soul."

