01:19:53,789 --> 01:19:55,165
# How I do #

1352
01:19:58,168 --> 01:20:04,466
- Tonight, the 34-stop tour ends.
- This is it, y'all.

1353
01:20:05,967 --> 01:20:07,177
This is it.

1354
01:20:11,056 --> 01:20:12,474
What has this journey been like?

1355
01:20:12,724 --> 01:20:15,101
What have you learned,
maybe about yourself?

1356
01:20:15,185 --> 01:20:17,771
And what has surprised you most
about your travels?

1357
01:20:18,146 --> 01:20:22,734
I've had the rare experience
to see the world in this way,

1358
01:20:22,818 --> 01:20:25,612
which is why I feel like
I've got to share with you all

1359
01:20:25,695 --> 01:20:28,949
that, you know,
the energy that's out there

1360
01:20:29,032 --> 01:20:31,660
is much better than what we see.

1361
01:20:32,661 --> 01:20:35,163
I wish people didn't feel badly,

1362
01:20:35,455 --> 01:20:38,208
because this country is good.

1363
01:20:38,542 --> 01:20:39,709
People are good.

1364
01:20:40,168 --> 01:20:41,545
People are decent.

1365
01:20:44,381 --> 01:20:45,841
I tell you what I'm nostalgic for.

1366
01:20:46,174 --> 01:20:48,468
I miss the opportunity we had

1367
01:20:48,552 --> 01:20:51,680
to have leaders
who talked to us about hope,

1368
01:20:52,097 --> 01:20:54,933
and the possibility of change,
which is what hope is.

1369
01:20:55,559 --> 01:20:56,560
Well...

1370
01:20:57,477 --> 01:21:00,063
here's what I've learned
just on this book tour.

1371
01:21:00,146 --> 01:21:03,525
You know, one of the things
we do miss about Barack Obama

1372
01:21:03,608 --> 01:21:05,861
is that he would get out into the country

1373
01:21:06,278 --> 01:21:08,363
and he would campaign around hope,

1374
01:21:08,446 --> 01:21:10,115
and he would fill arenas,

1375
01:21:10,198 --> 01:21:12,492
and then people
would come out and remember,

1376
01:21:12,576 --> 01:21:14,578
"Yeah. Yeah. Yeah."

1377
01:21:16,580 --> 01:21:18,039
"I do like this."

1378
01:21:19,624 --> 01:21:22,294
And then people would be surrounded
with each other,

1379
01:21:22,377 --> 01:21:24,379
of all different backgrounds,
and they would go,

1380
01:21:24,462 --> 01:21:26,339
"Yeah, I'm not alone in this.

1381
01:21:27,716 --> 01:21:31,177
I like this feeling of not being divided.

1382
01:21:31,261 --> 01:21:32,304
I do."

1383
01:21:33,513 --> 01:21:37,851
If we can open up a little bit more
to each other and share our stories,

1384
01:21:37,934 --> 01:21:39,519
our real stories,

1385
01:21:39,603 --> 01:21:41,563
that's what breaks down barriers.

1386
01:21:42,272 --> 01:21:44,024
But in order to do that,

1387
01:21:44,107 --> 01:21:46,860
you have to believe
that your story has value.

1388
01:21:47,652 --> 01:21:50,196
Be vulnerable. Dare to be vulnerable.

1389
01:21:51,990 --> 01:21:53,783
We're at a crossroads

1390
01:21:53,867 --> 01:21:55,702
of where we have to think about,

1391
01:21:55,785 --> 01:21:57,954
"Who are we as a nation?"

1392
01:21:58,788 --> 01:22:02,584
I remain hopeful
that people want better...

1393
01:22:03,793 --> 01:22:07,255
if not for themselves,
then for the next generation.

1394
01:22:09,883 --> 01:22:12,552
And that is my basic joy.

1395
01:22:12,636 --> 01:22:15,472
You know,
it gets back to mentoring others.

1396
01:22:15,555 --> 01:22:18,058
That's what I'm going to do
until people are like,

1397
01:22:18,141 --> 01:22:20,018
"OK, you're done, old lady."

1398
01:22:20,393 --> 01:22:22,562
I'll just be on stage in a wheelchair,

1399
01:22:22,646 --> 01:22:24,731
just going, "And another thing..."

1400
01:22:26,274 --> 01:22:29,194
You know? And they'll be, like,
"Oh, that little old Michelle Obama.

1401
01:22:29,277 --> 01:22:31,738
She's still just talking," you know?

1402
01:22:31,821 --> 01:22:36,034
I want to be the 90-year-old woman
that you just excuse, you know?

1403
01:22:39,037 --> 01:22:42,582
Ladies and gentlemen, join me in thanking
Michelle Obama for being here tonight.

1404
01:22:42,666 --> 01:22:44,376
Thank you all so much.

1405
01:23:10,151 --> 01:23:13,113
- I am becoming a strong...
- Yes.

1406
01:23:13,196 --> 01:23:15,532
- ...confident, fierce girl...
